INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  'fae4b22f-f563-4b94-b170-d5448fa43f82',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$pandas Data Cleaning — A 10-Line Pipeline for Nulls, Outliers, Types, and Dupes$escape$,
  $escape$Most pandas cleaning jobs hit the same four problems: missing values, wrong dtypes, outliers, and duplicates. Chain them into a single pipeline instead of scattering fixes across cells.

Start with `df.info()` to spot object columns that should be numeric — `pd.to_numeric(col, errors='coerce')` converts and flags failures as NaN in one pass. For nulls, `df.fillna()` works for constants, but `df.interpolate(method='linear')` is smarter for time-series gaps. Use `df.isna().sum()` first to decide strategy per column.

Outlier detection via IQR is robust: compute Q1/Q3 with `df.quantile()`, then boolean-index to clip or drop. For deduplication, `df.drop_duplicates(subset=[...], keep='last')` lets you target specific columns and control which row survives.

The key insight: order matters. Coerce types first (so numeric operations work), then handle nulls (so aggregations are correct), then remove outliers (on clean data), then deduplicate last (so you're comparing apples to apples).$escape$,
  $escape$import pandas as pd
import numpy as np

def clean(df: pd.DataFrame, num_cols: list[str], dedup_cols: list[str]) -> pd.DataFrame:
    # 1. Type coercion
    for c in num_cols:
        df[c] = pd.to_numeric(df[c], errors='coerce')
    # 2. Null handling — median fill for numeric
    df[num_cols] = df[num_cols].fillna(df[num_cols].median())
    # 3. IQR outlier removal
    Q1, Q3 = df[num_cols].quantile(0.25), df[num_cols].quantile(0.75)
    IQR = Q3 - Q1
    mask = ~((df[num_cols] < Q1 - 1.5 * IQR) | (df[num_cols] > Q3 + 1.5 * IQR)).any(axis=1)
    df = df[mask]
    # 4. Deduplication
    return df.drop_duplicates(subset=dedup_cols, keep='last').reset_index(drop=True)$escape$,
  $escape$python$escape$,
